programme.title: Law & Order

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Phobia. The killing of a gay man whose partner had adopted a son leads to a case that questions whether it was a hate crime

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Heartbreak City. When a demon steals Cupid's ring, he uses it to end all the relationships that were ever created by the angelic match-maker. So Cupid must convince the Halliwell sisters to help him get the ring back before love itself becomes a permanent victim

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Reckless Abandon. The girls protect a seemingly abandoned baby from a vengeful ghost

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Awakened. Piper contracts a rare tropical disease and slips into a coma, forcing Prue and Phoebe to cast a spell to awaken her. In the process, they cause the disease to spread throughout the hospital via a playful courier. There's one other frightening side effect---the sisters now can't sleep, which threatens to drive them insane. Leo: Brian Krause. Dan: Greg Vaughan. Jack: Lochlyn Munro. Piper: Holly Marie Combs. Prue: Shannen Doherty

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: The Werther Project. Sam searches for a magical box built by a former Men of Letters that may be able to cure Dean of the Mark of Cain. But the box contains a deadly alarm system that puts the brothers' lives in danger

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Angel Heart. Castiel tries to help Claire Novak find her mom who has been missing for years. He feels guilty for what he did to the Novak family and wants to make amends by reuniting Claire with her mother

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Dark Dynasty. Sam and Dean investigate a bizarre murder and realise the killer has the same tattoo as those from the Styne family. Meanwhile, Castiel acts a referee when Charlie and Rowena are forced to work together on the Book of the Damned

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: The Prisoner. Dean decides to take matters into his own hands when it comes to the Stynes, and Sam tries to come to terms with his decision

programme.title: Bones
programme.desc: The Fire in the Ice. Returning for a fourth season, Bones is a scientific crime drama with plenty of chemistry. Inspired by real-life forensic anthropologist and bestselling writer Kathy Reichs, the series follows bone-studying novelist Dr Temperance Brennan (Emily Deschanel) who is called on by the law to assist with murder cases. To her endless irritation, she is teamed with Special Agent Seeley Booth (David Boreanaz) of the FBI's Homicide Investigations Unit. The pair use their individual skills to piece together puzzling murders, and their individual personalities to spar off each other. Also starring Michaela Conlin as Brennan's best friend Angela Montenegro, Eric Millegan as assistant Zack Addy, TJ Thyne as insect expert Dr Jack Hodgins and Jonathan Adams as Brennan's boss Dr Daniel Goodman

programme.title: Bones
programme.desc: The Hero in the Hold. The Grave Digger returns, turning its attention, and shovel, to Booth. Buried alive with just 24 hours' worth of oxygen, can Brennan get to him in time?

programme.title: Tower Heist
programme.desc: Workers at a posh Central Park condominium plot to steal back their pensions from the thieving Wall Street billionaire who's about to get away with the ultimate white-collar crime in this heist comedy starring Ben Stiller and Eddie Murphy

programme.title: Rush Hour
programme.desc: The fastest hands in the East meet the biggest mouth in the West when legendary martial arts daredevil Jackie Chan teams with comedic powerhouse Chris Tucker in Rush Hour. When Hong Kong police detective inspector Lee's favourite pupil is kidnapped in America, the dedicated cop and martial arts genius travels to the United States to find her. Unhappy to have a meddling outsider, the FBI assigns reckless, arrogant and infuriating LAPD detective James Carter to baby-sit Lee--and keep him away from the investigation. But these two very different cops will stop at nothing to find the missing girl

programme.title: The Dunk King
programme.desc: Finals. Finals of the second annual contest to crown the world's top dunker. Top prize is $100,000. Judges include Charles Barkley, Julius Erving, Shaquille O'Neal, Brent Barry and Nate Robinson

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Animal Pragmatism. Phoebe discovers that her university study group has used a love spell to turn three animals into men on Valentine's Day. The men, however, have retained their animal instincts and begin attacking innocent students

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Pardon My Past. Phoebe experiences flashes of a past life when she and her sisters were cousins in the 1930s. However, in this life, Phoebe was evil and power mad

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Give Me a Sign. Phoebe helps Piper to choose between Dan and Leo by casting a spell that reveals which of them is her true love. Bane breaks out of jail and kidnaps Prue so that she can use her powers to save him from the powerful demons that are chasing him

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Brother's Keeper. Season 10 ends with Dean making a shocking decision regarding the Mark of Cain that may change not only his life but Sam's too

programme.sub-title: Out of the Darkness, Into the Fire

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Form and Void. Dean helps Jenna, the nurse he met after the Darkness fell, get back home safely, but she soon falls into dangerous hands. Meanwhile, Sam deals with a town infected by a mysterious and deadly gas that is turning the locals into monsters

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: The Bad Seed. Rowena tries to consolidate her power to protect herself from the Winchesters, while Sam and Dean search for a missing baby connected to the Darkness. Meanwhile, Castiel struggles to heal; and Crowley tries to find a way to use the Darkness for his own personal gain

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Baby. Seen entirely from the point of view of the Impala, Sam and Dean go on a road trip to fight monsters and demons

programme.title: Jack the Giant Slayer
programme.desc: A young farmhand comes into possession of some magic beans but, when planted, they open up a gateway to a land inhabited by angry giants

programme.title: Man of Steel
programme.desc: After being sent to Earth from planet Krypton by his parents with a special object from his home planet in tow, Clark Kent grows up with the help of his earthly adopted parents and later assumes the identity of Superman and sets out to defend Earth from the villainous General Zod

programme.title: Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Pilot. An upcoming heist is planned and Joshua "J" Cody discovers the intense nature of his estranged grandmother in the series premiere of this crime drama about a teen plunging into danger when he moves in with his wild relatives in a surf community

programme.title: Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: We Don't Hurt People. Fallout from a heist impacts the Codys when they discover not all went as planned. Smurf enlists the guys to tie up loose ends, but a deepening rivalry threatens the job. Meanwhile, Pope grows increasingly volatile

programme.title: Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Stay Close, Stick Together. Craig recovers from a wound as Baz and Craig sharpen focus on old associates in Mexico. Meanwhile, Pope needs cash and draws Deran and J into a job without Smurf's knowledge, and Deran sends a terrifying message to J

programme.title: Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Dead to Me. Pope's birthday approaches as Smurf probes whether the boys are playing by her rules. Meanwhile, J makes discoveries about his mother's estrangement from the family

programme.title: Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Flesh Is Weak. Pope goes to extreme measures when Deran won't return home. Meanwhile, Baz comes up with an idea for Cody's next job; J goes out with his teacher; and Smurf faces her past

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Ego. An investigator with the State Attorney General's Office is found dead in the Manhattan river, leading Detectives Briscoe and Green into a web of high level intrigue

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: White Lie. Two people are found dead, and the subsequent investigation quickly segues from murder to drugs. But Caryn refuses to cooperate with the D.A.'s office until McCoy (Sam Waterston) backs her into a potentially fatal corner

programme.desc: Whiplash. Two personal injury attorneys go on trial, accused of masterminding an insurance fraud scam involving staged rear-end automobile accidents

programme.title: Law & Order

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Brother's Keeper. A criminal well known to detectives Briscoe (Jerry Orbach) and Green (Jesse L. Martin) may have been responsible for the murder of a businessman. programme.title: Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Child Care. Smurf does what's needed to keep the family intact when Pope tests positive for drugs. Also, Baz assembles his brothers to rob a home as part of his larger scheme, and J faces a moral dilemma
